  "prompt": "\"CAS PRES CHQ\" what does this SBI statement message mean?",
  "response": "The message \"CAS PRES CHQ\" in an SBI (State Bank of India) statement likely stands for \"Cash Present Cheque.\" This indicates that a cheque has been presented for processing or payment. It usually refers to a transaction where a cheque you issued has been processed by the bank, and the amount specified on the cheque has been debited from your account. Always make sure to verify such entries with your own records or contact your bank if you have any doubts or discrepancies.",
